Class Flight

java.lang.Object
Flight
Direct Known Subclasses:
Domestic, International
public abstract class Flight extends Object
Flight class to encapsule all attributes and methods necessary to represent a flight from the consumable CSV file.

      public Flight(int idIn, String flightNumberIn, Airport origAirportIn, Airport destAirportIn, String depaDateIn, String depaTimeIn, int durationIn, int distanceIn, int timeDiffIn, String arrDateIn, String arrTimeIn, String flightTypeIn, double surchargeIn, boolean isFoodServedIn, double routeCostIn, int minerPointsIn, int totalSeatsIn, int firstSeatsIn, int businSeatsIn, int mainSeatsIn, double firstPriceIn, double businPriceIn, double mainPriceIn)
      Constructor that enables the filling of all the attributes from the CSV file. It also calculates the correct duration of the flight at the end. [Taken from Ruben Carmona]
      Parameters:
      idIn - the flight's ID
      flightNumberIn - the flight's number
      origAirportIn - the flight's origin airport name
      destAirportIn - the flight's destination airport name
      depaDateIn - the flight's departure date
      depaTimeIn - the flight's departure time
      durationIn - the flight's duration
      distanceIn - the flight's distance
      timeDiffIn - the flight's time zone difference
      arrDateIn - the flight's arrival date
      arrTimeIn - the flight's arrival time
      flightTypeIn - the flight's type
      surchargeIn - the flight's surcharge
      isFoodServedIn - the flight's food served status
      routeCostIn - the flight's route cost
      minerPointsIn - the flight's miner points
      totalSeatsIn - the flight's total seats
      firstSeatsIn - the flight's number of seats in first class
      businSeatsIn - the flight's number of seats in business class
      mainSeatsIn - the flight's number of seats in main cabin class
      firstPriceIn - the flight's first class price
      businPriceIn - the flight's business class price
      mainPriceIn - the flight's main cabin price
